column5: Gas?...check. Plug in?.....check. Batteries charged?.....check. Safety equipment?.....check. Fishing gear?....check. OFC sticker?.......yep. All set to go.  Plug is in now. HDS5 is mounted on dash and boat is vaccumed and ready for slimin.
Woo hoo! reserve me a spot!
Yesterday afternoon it was gorgeous here.
Small world. think I know where your boat is. Is that where you live?  I used to live on 5th Ave.
Good luck, Blair.  I'll be down on Restoule for most of the weekend.
The Silver Bass are here... not full stream yet but are here..  Don't ask me how I know  Randy
I think I know.  Sounds like a trip for the following weekend.
hey guys i am heading up to Lavigne for the weekend just wondering what the water levels are like.thanks.

I'm heading to the annual meeting of the Eagle Lake Hookers Club in Vermilion Bay on Eagle Lake tomorrow morning/ As the original poster did his check list so did I.  Friday morning should see us heading into Clearwater Lake for lake trout. Then on Saturday its walleye time.  Those brewskis on the front porch of the cabin are going to taste great.
Plugs in? check...  I put the plug in right?  Check....  Ok one more time... Yep plugs in, let's go FISHING!!
Good luck Man.. Friday morn for me.(NO KIDDS   YEEAA)   SHUT UP AND FISH
